he threw a-- a yogurt

10:03.307 --> 10:04.339
at his assistant's face.

10:04.408 --> 10:06.608
(SCOFFS) He got fired
'cause he threw a yogurt?

10:06.677 --> 10:07.876
-Jesus.
-DAPHNE: Yes. You can't throw

10:07.945 --> 10:09.010
a yogurt at someone's face.

10:09.079 --> 10:10.946
CAMERON: It's his assistant.
Who cares?

10:11.015 --> 10:13.315
I ran into his wife at the gym.
She's awful.

10:13.384 --> 10:14.515
CAMERON: Oh, my God.

10:14.584 --> 10:17.085
DAPHNE: Two kids
in private school.

10:17.154 --> 10:19.021
I mean, his family can help them
a little bit, but--

10:19.090 --> 10:22.990
Christ. When did the world
become run by nuns?

10:23.059 --> 10:26.128
I mean, you're not even supposed
to succeed anymore, right?

10:26.197 --> 10:27.796
-DAPHNE: Mm-hmm.
-'Cause if you succeed,

10:27.865 --> 10:29.832
oh, shit, you might make
someone else feel bad.

10:29.900 --> 10:31.533
-(DAPHNE CHUCKLES)
-You might cause harm

10:31.602 --> 10:33.436
to all the sad losers
in the world.

10:33.505 --> 10:35.240
(SCOFFS) You're an idiot.

10:39.710 --> 10:42.314
♪ (TENSE MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

10:54.659 --> 10:57.396
♪ (MUSIC CONTINUES) ♪

11:06.403 --> 11:07.668
-Hey.
-ALBIE: Hey.

11:07.737 --> 11:09.439
-How'd you sleep?
♪ (MUSIC FADES) ♪

11:09.508 --> 11:11.674
Fine. Um, Dad?

11:11.743 --> 11:13.012
DOMINIC DI GRASSO: Yeah?

11:14.145 --> 11:15.114
(SIGHS)

11:18.249 --> 11:20.219
I need 50,000 euros.

11:22.086 --> 11:24.990
(CHUCKLES) Fifty thousand euros?

11:26.557 --> 11:27.792
What for?

11:31.563 --> 11:33.265
Oh, no, not for that girl.

11:36.100 --> 11:37.699
Well, forget it.

11:37.768 --> 11:39.601
I have all the bank account
information,

11:39.670 --> 11:42.337
so you can just
call your accountant

11:42.406 --> 11:43.839
and have him wire the money.

11:43.908 --> 11:46.208
Yeah. Sure. I'll just call him
right now. Yeah.

11:46.277 --> 11:47.379
Gimme the--

11:49.314 --> 11:50.315
No.

11:54.151 --> 11:56.917
-What?
-You can make someone's life.

11:56.986 --> 11:59.721
Fifty thousand euros? And--
and you just met this girl,

11:59.790 --> 12:01.957
-like, what, three days ago?
-So what?

12:02.026 --> 12:04.860
Come on, Albie. Get real.

12:04.929 --> 12:06.596
Lots of people need help
in the world.

12:06.665 --> 12:07.963
I'm not an NGO.

12:08.032 --> 12:10.799
You don't need it.
It's nothing to you.

12:10.868 --> 12:14.206
No, it's nothing to you
'cause you don't work for money.

12:15.406 --> 12:17.142
It's pretty much nothing to you.

12:19.276 --> 12:21.510
I mean, what? You're just gonna
go through life trying to rescue

12:21.579 --> 12:23.345
every desperate girl
you come across?

12:23.414 --> 12:24.512
Maybe. Yeah.

12:24.581 --> 12:28.520
Well, good luck with that.
Don't expect me to subsidize.

12:30.554 --> 12:33.993
Think of it as a karmic payment.

12:35.093 --> 12:36.996
-A karmic payment?
-ALBIE: Yeah.

12:38.362 --> 12:41.000
-For what?
-For all the shit you've done.

12:52.844 --> 12:54.009
Ten thousand euros.

12:54.078 --> 12:56.945
-Are we negotiating?
-No. I don't know. I mean--

12:57.014 --> 12:58.880
What-- She doesn't need
50,000 euros.

12:58.949 --> 13:01.016
-ALBIE: Yes, she does.
-Why does she need it?

13:01.085 --> 13:02.417
There's a dude stalking her.

13:02.486 --> 13:08.961
You saw him.
And she's stuck and-- Whatever.

13:10.261 --> 13:13.995
I just-- Fifty thousand dollars.
I can't. I could never--

13:14.064 --> 13:16.098
-not in good conscience ever--
-ALBIE: Conscience?

13:16.167 --> 13:19.338
Now you have a conscience?
Over this?

13:23.107 --> 13:26.311
Just do it. Just give it.

13:28.579 --> 13:30.913
And then what?
Are you gonna have

13:30.982 --> 13:32.981
some kind of relationship
with this girl?

13:33.050 --> 13:36.384
Why not, you know? I like her.

13:36.453 --> 13:39.058
We've been talking
about her coming to visit L.A.

13:40.124 --> 13:44.059
Come on, man. Albie. I mean--

13:44.128 --> 13:45.688
How are you gonna
make it in life

13:45.757 --> 13:48.567
-if you're this big a mark?
-I'm not a mark.

13:56.341 --> 13:57.943
(EXHALES DEEPLY)

14:02.713 --> 14:04.283
I'll help you out with Mom.

14:07.918 --> 14:10.052
-♪ (SOFT MUSIC PLAYING) ♪
-Give me 50...

14:10.121 --> 14:11.924
and I'll help you with Mom.

14:14.391 --> 14:16.856
-How are you gonna help me?
-I don't know.

14:17.729 --> 14:21.066
I'll tell her how sorry you are

14:21.966 --> 14:23.965
and how this whole trip,

14:24.034 --> 14:25.867
all you could think about
was her,

14:25.936 --> 14:29.474
and how it seems like
you've really changed.

14:30.808 --> 14:32.011
Yadda, yadda.

14:33.344 --> 14:34.346
You would do that?

14:40.251 --> 14:42.417
-Morning.
-DOMINIC: Morning.

14:42.485 --> 14:43.985
BERT DI GRASSO:
What are we talking about?

14:44.054 --> 14:46.158
-Nothing.
-Nothing.

14:49.359 --> 14:54.633
I had a dream that we went
to visit our relatives.

14:56.333 --> 14:58.200
They turned out to be
a bunch of banshees

14:58.269 --> 15:00.102
and chased us out of town.

15:00.171 --> 15:03.976
♪ (INTRIGUING MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

15:12.951 --> 15:15.984
(IN ITALIAN)

15:16.053 --> 15:19.058
ISABELLA: Ah. Wow. (CHUCKLES)

15:20.324 --> 15:22.261
(ISABELLA THANKING IN ITALIAN)

15:23.961 --> 15:25.297
-(RESPONDS IN ITALIAN)
-Okay.

15:26.531 --> 15:28.597
-Ciao.
-Ciao.

15:28.666 --> 15:31.401
ISABELLA:

15:31.470 --> 15:33.305
-Ah, no?
-No.

15:35.840 --> 15:37.109
ISABELLA: Ah, okay.

15:39.877 --> 15:41.080
(CHUCKLES)

15:46.484 --> 15:47.552
(CHUCKLES)

15:53.358 --> 15:54.326
Ah!

15:59.097 --> 16:01.797
-Sì.
-(SQUEALS) Grazie, grazie.

16:01.866 --> 16:03.602
(THANKS PROFUSELY IN ITALIAN)

16:07.672 --> 16:08.740
(CHUCKLES)

16:12.744 --> 16:14.209
Salvatore.

16:14.278 --> 16:16.712
Salvatore. Salvato--

16:16.781 --> 16:18.017
Salvatore.

16:18.683 --> 16:19.651
Scusa, eh.

16:31.796 --> 16:32.764
Grazie.

16:43.107 --> 16:47.079
(URGES IN ITALIAN)

16:49.581 --> 16:50.813
(SIGHS)

16:50.882 --> 16:54.350
(MATTEO GIVING
INSTRUCTIONS IN ITALIAN)

16:54.419 --> 16:56.151
(RATTLING)

16:56.220 --> 16:59.224
(MATTEO CONTINUES
GIVING INSTRUCTIONS IN ITALIAN)

17:00.657 --> 17:04.860
(MATTEO CONTINUES
GIVING INSTRUCTIONS IN ITALIAN)

17:04.929 --> 17:06.531
(MATTEO URGING IN ITALIAN)

17:07.799 --> 17:10.769
♪ (INTRIGUING MUSIC PLAYING) ♪

17:32.857 --> 17:35.627
TANYA: (IN ENGLISH)
Hello? Hello?

18:00.351 --> 18:02.187
-What are you doing?
-(GASPS)

18:03.054 --> 18:04.619
-Oh, hi.
-Hi.

18:04.688 --> 18:08.289
You know,
I came in here last night,

18:08.358 --> 18:10.921
you know, and I saw this photo.

18:10.990 --> 18:14.566
And I thought I dreamt it,
but here it is.

18:16.133 --> 18:17.469
I mean, who is this?

18:19.704 --> 18:20.672
Steve.

18:22.707 --> 18:24.406
Oh.

18:24.475 --> 18:26.474
He worked on a dude ranch
I stumbled on

18:26.543 --> 18:31.346
when I was bumming around
in my aspiring Kerouac days.

18:31.415 --> 18:34.583
We used to go fly-fishing
and drop acid together.

18:34.652 --> 18:35.918
(CHUCKLES)

18:35.987 --> 18:37.385
What ever happened to him?

18:37.454 --> 18:39.387
Do you know?
I don't really know.

18:39.456 --> 18:42.661
Lost touch. Haven't spoken
to him in decades.

18:43.527 --> 18:48.497
I mean, my God.
He looks just like Greg.

18:48.566 --> 18:51.270
-Greg?
-TANYA: My husband.

18:51.836 --> 18:53.505
Only he has hair.

18:54.238 --> 18:55.440
(CHUCKLES)

18:56.540 --> 18:58.477
Well,
the resemblance is uncanny.

19:00.144 --> 19:01.610
Well, we're heading out.

19:01.679 --> 19:04.246
We need to be at the dock
in half an hour.

19:04.315 --> 19:06.815
Matteo is staying back,
unfortunately,

19:06.884 --> 19:08.750
but he wanted to say goodbye.

19:08.819 --> 19:13.525
-Arrivederci, Tanya.
-TANYA: Oh. My God, Matteo.

19:13.891 --> 19:15.390
(CHUCKLES)

19:15.459 --> 19:16.657
(CRIES) Buona fortuna.

19:16.726 --> 19:19.961
-TANYA: (CHUCKLES) Oh.
-Buona fortuna. (CHUCKLES)

19:20.030 --> 19:21.163
TANYA: Hey.

19:21.232 --> 19:22.701
-Shall we?
-TANYA: Oh. Yeah.

19:23.334 --> 19:24.665
He's really crying.

19:24.734 --> 19:27.970
Yes. Italians, they tend
to get a little overwrought.

19:28.039 --> 19:33.412
♪ (DRAMATIC OPERA MUSIC
PLAYING) ♪

19:38.783 --> 19:43.422
(WAVES ROARING FAINTLY)

19:48.760 --> 19:50.262
♪ (MUSIC CONCLUDES) ♪

19:52.196 --> 19:53.398
(SIGHS)

20:00.838 --> 20:01.806
What's wrong?

20:03.341 --> 20:04.609
You fucked him.

20:05.910 --> 20:08.576
-What?
-I know what you did.

20:08.645 --> 20:10.112
You fucked him
to get back at me,

20:10.181 --> 20:11.583
but I did nothing wrong.

20:13.184 --> 20:15.587
-Are you okay?
-I know you did something.

20:16.120 --> 20:17.419
I didn't.

20:17.488 --> 20:19.524
You're lying.
You're not a good liar.

20:20.490 --> 20:23.425
Because I'm not lying
and I don't lie.

20:23.494 --> 20:26.461
You just called him an idiot
at breakfast.

20:26.530 --> 20:28.363
That was the tell.
You would not have done that

20:28.432 --> 20:29.797
if something hadn't happened
between you.

20:29.866 --> 20:32.935
-That doesn't make any sense.
-Stop fucking with me, Harper.

20:33.004 --> 20:34.837
I can forgive you,
but just be honest with me.

20:34.906 --> 20:37.272
-I saw you at the fucking bar.
-What bar?

20:37.341 --> 20:38.673
ETHAN SPILLER: You know the bar.

20:38.742 --> 20:40.675
I was in the water
and you guys were doing shots

20:40.744 --> 20:42.477
and flirting and whispering
to each other.

20:42.546 --> 20:45.214
And then I come up here
and the fucking door is latched?

20:45.283 --> 20:48.387
-Why was the door latched?
-I don't know.

20:51.222 --> 20:52.120
Yeah, right.

20:52.189 --> 20:56.857
I don't know.
You're reading into it, okay?

20:56.926 --> 20:58.893
It-- It's not like you found
a condom on the couch.

20:58.962 --> 21:01.530
-(SCOFFS)
-The difference is,
I didn't do anything!

21:01.599 --> 21:02.667
Did I?

21:03.700 --> 21:06.034
-How do I know?
-Because I fucking told you.

21:06.103 --> 21:09.337
You asked me so I told you.
I told you the whole truth.

21:09.406 --> 21:12.407
Well, I'm telling you
I didn't do anything, okay?

21:12.476 --> 21:14.579
Haven't I always been honest
with you?

21:23.120 --> 21:25.457
Yeah. But you're lying now.

21:29.293 --> 21:32.331
-Ethan, fuck off.
-Just be honest with me.

21:33.864 --> 21:36.768
Just be honest with me.
Just tell me what happened.

21:38.335 --> 21:39.567
I can't move on from this

21:39.636 --> 21:41.640
until you tell me
exactly the truth.

21:42.241 --> 21:43.842
(SIGHS)

21:52.083 --> 21:54.750
(SNIFFLES, SIGHS)

21:54.819 --> 21:56.455
(BREATHES HEAVILY)

21:58.657 --> 22:02.427
Okay. Okay. (BREATHES DEEPLY)

22:05.997 --> 22:07.967
Okay, we did shots at the bar.

22:09.267 --> 22:11.066
-Mm-hmm.
-HARPER SPILLER:
And... (INHALES)

22:11.135 --> 22:14.435
(BREATHES HEAVILY)

22:14.504 --> 22:16.504
And, yeah,
I was really mad at you

22:16.573 --> 22:18.406
because of the hookers
and the condom

22:18.475 --> 22:20.375
-and the whole situation.
-And then?

22:20.444 --> 22:23.048
HARPER: (BREATHES HEAVILY)
And then--

22:26.484 --> 22:29.521
